WEBVTT

00:01.420 --> 00:02.399
There are two kinds of folks

00:02.426 --> 00:04.026
who sit around thinking
about how to kill people:

00:04.360 --> 00:06.086
Psychopaths and mystery writers.

00:06.324 --> 00:07.346
I'm the kind that pays better.

00:07.747 --> 00:08.347
Who am I?

00:08.436 --> 00:09.575
I'm Rick Castle.

00:09.576 --> 00:09.976
Castle.

00:10.010 --> 00:10.670
Castle.

00:10.671 --> 00:12.671
I really am ruggedly
handsome, aren't I?

00:12.817 --> 00:15.007
Every writer needs inspiration.
And I found mine.

00:15.217 --> 00:16.036
Detective Kate Beckett.

00:16.071 --> 00:17.091
- Beckett.
- Beckett.

00:17.126 --> 00:19.032
- Nikki Heat?
- The character he's basing on you.

00:19.078 --> 00:20.564
And thanks to my
friendship with the mayor,

00:20.565 --> 00:21.565
I get to be on her case.

00:21.599 --> 00:23.542
I would be happy to
let you spank me.

00:23.577 --> 00:24.453
And together, we catch killers

00:25.401 --> 00:26.389
we make a pretty good team,
you know?

00:26.390 --> 00:27.390
Like Starsky and Hutch.

00:27.524 --> 00:28.218
Turner and Hooch.

00:28.581 --> 00:30.084
You do remind me a little of Hooch.

00:30.783 --> 00:32.080
Ahh.

00:32.081 --> 00:33.908
You meet up with
that baby last night?

00:33.909 --> 00:35.870
Yeah. Yeah? No sleep again?

00:35.871 --> 00:38.598
Never. No sleep, baby.
That's how we do it.

00:46.025 --> 00:48.308
Chef? Chef?

00:49.089 --> 00:50.193
Check his pulse.

00:50.721 --> 00:52.384
Ah!

00:52.504 --> 00:54.222
Whoa.

00:54.642 --> 00:56.626
What broke? A stupid glass.

00:56.887 --> 00:58.673
Remind me to get smarter glasses.

00:58.793 --> 01:01.511
Somehow I feel that the glass
is not quite the problem.

01:01.512 --> 01:03.886
I got invited to the
Hamptons with Lacey's family

01:04.006 --> 01:06.343
and a couple of other friends.
Well, that sounds like fun.

01:07.612 --> 01:08.996
So why do you look like someone

01:09.116 --> 01:10.167
who just got voted off the island?

01:10.428 --> 01:11.729
A.P. tests are next week,

01:11.849 --> 01:13.595
so I really need to
study all weekend.

01:13.971 --> 01:15.518
But I really want to
go to the Hamptons.

01:15.843 --> 01:18.026
The eternal struggle
between work and play.

01:18.273 --> 01:19.675
The trick is, when you grow up,

01:20.241 --> 01:21.773
find work that feels like play.

01:22.579 --> 01:24.010
Speaking of work...

01:24.742 --> 01:26.366
What are you doing up
and dressed so early?

01:26.486 --> 01:28.565
Oh, no reason. Just thought I'd
get an early start to my day.

01:28.685 --> 01:30.444
Mm-hmm. Bye.

01:32.000 --> 01:38.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:40.588 --> 01:42.834
All right. So, um,
I'll see you tomorrow night?

01:42.954 --> 01:44.754
Yeah. Good. Okay. Okay.

01:45.342 --> 01:46.708
See ya.

01:47.456 --> 01:49.262
What's Demming doing
in our break room?

01:49.382 --> 01:50.666
Is there something wrong
with the coffee downstairs?

01:50.786 --> 01:52.069
Well, you're the one who bought us

01:52.189 --> 01:53.209
the Cappuccino machine, Castle.

01:53.210 --> 01:54.759
Yes, but I bought it for homicide

01:54.879 --> 01:56.729
not the entire precinct. Oh.

01:57.179 --> 01:58.412
What's tomorrow night? What?

01:59.907 --> 02:00.789
Oh, Tom was wondering

02:00.909 --> 02:02.654
if I wanted to get
together tomorrow night.

02:03.941 --> 02:05.076
Why? Is that a problem?

02:05.582 --> 02:06.690
Why would I have a
problem with that?

02:07.054 --> 02:08.094
Hmm.

02:08.214 --> 02:09.747
Excuse me.

02:09.747 --> 02:10.975
Beckett.

02:12.117 --> 02:13.949
Okay. Be right there.

02:15.317 --> 02:17.250
Tom.

02:19.334 --> 02:21.257
Right. Right. The murder is at Q3?

02:21.620 --> 02:23.066
This place has only
been open three months.

02:23.186 --> 02:24.252
<i>I</i> can't even get a
reservation here.

02:24.372 --> 02:25.785
I've been dying to eat here.

02:25.905 --> 02:27.186
Well, evidently,
you're not the only one.

02:27.575 --> 02:28.934
Where are we? In the kitchen.

02:29.339 --> 02:31.609
Victim's name is Balthazar Wolf.
He's the head chef here.

02:32.390 --> 02:34.856
Big bad Wolf? Winner of
"Kitchen Wars," season six?

02:34.976 --> 02:36.046
I know. Right?

02:36.166 --> 02:38.728
Aw, man. I never got to taste
his Foie gras sandwich.

02:39.125 --> 02:41.236
He was found this morning
by the pastry chef--

02:41.356 --> 02:43.318
Spike Ridenhauer-
and one of the dishwashers--

02:43.438 --> 02:44.472
Juan Costa.

02:46.184 --> 02:47.326
Oh.

02:47.327 --> 02:48.860
Castle, stop!

02:49.245 --> 02:51.707
D-do you not see the little
orange cones around the body?

02:51.982 --> 02:53.210
Is that actually his hand?

02:53.330 --> 02:55.621
That's the effect of L-N-2...

02:56.480 --> 02:57.434
Commonly known

02:57.554 --> 03:00.079
as liquid nitrogen,
a cryogenic refrigerant.

03:00.600 --> 03:02.795
It instantly freezes anything
it comes in touch with,

03:02.915 --> 03:05.398
including Mr. Wolf-
made him fragile as glass.

03:05.922 --> 03:08.984
This is both literally
and figuratively cool.

03:10.185 --> 03:12.440
Uh, Wolf was a follower
of molecular gastronomy.

03:12.686 --> 03:15.589
It's using the science
to manipulate the...

03:18.061 --> 03:19.075
And you don't care.

03:19.562 --> 03:22.164
It's usually pretty safe
unless someone dumps it on you.

03:22.477 --> 03:23.439
Time of death?

03:23.771 --> 03:27.077
Well, all our normal indicators...

03:27.197 --> 03:29.539
Are contaminated by the L-N-2.

03:29.858 --> 03:31.826
I'll see what I can do
once I get to the morgue.

03:31.946 --> 03:35.018
But, uh, we're gonna have
to let him thaw a bit

03:35.019 --> 03:36.079
before we can move him.

03:36.199 --> 03:37.777
Looks like there was a struggle.

03:38.153 --> 03:38.862
Robbery?

03:38.982 --> 03:41.556
No, no sign of forced entry,
nothing's missing.

03:41.557 --> 03:44.268
According to Mr.
Ridenhauer and Mr. Costa here,

03:44.629 --> 03:45.713
our victim stayed at the restaurant

03:45.833 --> 03:46.978
long after everyone else had left.

03:47.098 --> 03:48.077
And what time was that?

03:48.197 --> 03:49.101
It was around 11:00.

03:49.221 --> 03:50.821
One of our clients had
special ordered a cake,

03:50.941 --> 03:52.336
and Wolf stayed behind
to finish it up.

03:52.929 --> 03:53.993
Aren't you the pastry chef?

03:54.113 --> 03:56.205
Yeah, but I don't do crazy
stuff like Wolf does.

03:56.325 --> 03:58.078
I just, uh, I made the cushion,

03:58.198 --> 04:00.451
and he sculpted the crown, uh,
the heart and the jewels.

04:00.941 --> 04:02.683
That's probably why he had
the rotary evaporator out

04:02.803 --> 04:04.034
and the liquid nitrogen.

04:04.154 --> 04:05.725
All right, after Perlmutter
gets the body out,

04:05.845 --> 04:07.750
I'm gonna want C.S.U. to come in
and sweep for fibers and prints.

04:07.870 --> 04:08.461
Yeah, yeah.

04:08.581 --> 04:10.280
Yo, Beckett. The owner's here.

04:10.400 --> 04:12.754
Say there's been an
accident. Madison?

04:14.620 --> 04:16.742
Becks? What are you doing here?

04:17.103 --> 04:18.902
I'm a homicide Detective.

04:19.190 --> 04:21.223
Shut the front door. I know.

04:21.224 --> 04:23.180
I-I know, right?

04:23.455 --> 04:25.276
What a messed up way
for us to reconnect.

04:25.396 --> 04:27.071
Madison Queller,
this is Richard Castle.

04:27.191 --> 04:28.107
Hi.

04:28.227 --> 04:29.284
Hi. Please call me Rick.

04:29.404 --> 04:30.912
How do you two know each other?
High School.

04:31.032 --> 04:32.541
Ninth grade French.

04:33.018 --> 04:35.419
I can't believe the biggest
scofflaw at Stuy became a cop.

04:35.539 --> 04:37.049
Yeah.

04:38.386 --> 04:39.862
So I'm gonna need
contact information

04:39.863 --> 04:41.427
for all the restaurant staff.

04:41.547 --> 04:42.437
Come on, Becks.

04:42.557 --> 04:43.569
You think somebody here
might have done it?

04:43.689 --> 04:45.680
You know, no forced entry
usually means that the killer

04:45.800 --> 04:47.649
either knew the chef or
was someone who had keys.

04:47.769 --> 04:50.268
So I'm gonna need alibis
from everyone, including you.

04:50.571 --> 04:52.205
Sorry. No. No, I, uh...

04:52.206 --> 04:53.173
I understand.

04:53.621 --> 04:55.383
I was at a party
until the wee hours.

04:55.642 --> 04:56.684
Lots of people saw me.,

04:56.804 --> 04:58.157
Now did you know if
Wolf had any enemies

04:58.277 --> 04:59.672
anyone that wanted to do him harm?

04:59.976 --> 05:01.886
He was the bad boy
America loved to hate.

05:02.189 --> 05:03.714
I was a guest judge.
That's how we met.

05:04.336 --> 05:05.496
Seriously?

05:05.616 --> 05:07.124
You never heard of "Kitchen Wars"?

05:07.369 --> 05:08.599
Uh...

05:09.334 --> 05:12.677
No. I don't really get a
lot of time to watch tv.

05:12.797 --> 05:14.792
This from the girl
who'd spend hours

05:14.912 --> 05:16.762
watching "Saved By
the Bell" reruns?

05:17.268 --> 05:18.306
Really?

05:18.826 --> 05:20.595
What else did she
spend hours doing?

05:21.049 --> 05:22.379
Castle, real crime scene.

05:22.499 --> 05:24.464
Not mystery writer
research time, okay?

05:25.101 --> 05:27.355
Did you notice anything
unusual about Wolf lately?

05:27.703 --> 05:28.699
Anything at all.

05:28.819 --> 05:30.185
There was one thing.

05:30.547 --> 05:32.440
Wolf usually worked nonstop.

05:32.818 --> 05:34.522
You couldn't tear him
away from the kitchen.

05:34.977 --> 05:36.553
But for the last couple of weeks,

05:36.673 --> 05:38.512
he'd disappear around 3:00,

05:38.513 --> 05:40.581
and come back just in
time to prep at 5:00.

05:40.941 --> 05:41.799
Did he say where he was going?

05:41.919 --> 05:43.343
No. He said it was personal.

05:43.463 --> 05:45.165
Hey, guys. I found something.

05:46.457 --> 05:48.545
Juan the dishwasher was the
last one here last night,

05:48.665 --> 05:50.005
and he swears he finished
every single dish.

05:50.125 --> 05:52.467
Two dirty bowls,
two spoons and a soup pot?

05:52.901 --> 05:54.496
Looks like Wolf had
some late-night company.

05:55.416 --> 05:57.513
It's popcorn soup.
It's Domingo's specialty.

05:57.800 --> 05:58.939
Domingo? Our line chef. .

05:59.200 --> 06:00.615
He must have come back
after everybody left.

06:00.904 --> 06:02.948
That means he's the last one
to have seen Wolf alive.

06:03.068 --> 06:04.644
Do you have an address? Of course.

06:04.764 --> 06:06.318
All right, track
down Domingo and see

06:06.438 --> 06:08.000
why he was here so
late and what he saw.

06:08.862 --> 06:11.479
I'll also need the contact
info for Wolf's next of kin.

06:15.749 --> 06:16.949
High School friend, huh?

06:17.069 --> 06:18.843
I bet she knows where all
your bodies are buried.

06:19.121 --> 06:20.365
You can dig all you want, Castle.

06:20.485 --> 06:22.494
My secrets are safe with her.
How can you be sure?

06:22.614 --> 06:23.933
Because whatever
she knows about me,

06:24.295 --> 06:25.683
I know worse about her.

06:26.624 --> 06:28.601
We used to hang out,
big group of us,

06:28.721 --> 06:29.630
had a good time.

06:29.933 --> 06:32.068
And... what's a good time?

06:32.069 --> 06:33.643
Well, if you don't know by now,

06:33.763 --> 06:35.364
I'm sure it's too
late to show you one.

06:36.541 --> 06:37.973
Here's Wolf's emergency contact--

06:38.093 --> 06:39.127
David Nicolaides.

06:39.472 --> 06:41.479
Wolf didn't have any real family.

06:41.889 --> 06:44.332
He spent most of his childhood
in and out of foster homes,

06:44.452 --> 06:47.383
which is why we're listed as,
uh, next of kin.

06:48.567 --> 06:50.919
My girlfriend Cecily and I are
about as close as it gets.

06:51.599 --> 06:52.743
They were like brothers.

06:53.050 --> 06:54.517
How long did you know each other?

06:54.864 --> 06:55.819
Since our teens.

06:56.218 --> 06:58.028
My dad gave him a job in
our restaurant as a busboy,

06:58.148 --> 07:00.404
uh, when he got out of juvie.

07:01.011 --> 07:03.690
It didn't take long to tell that
he had a real gift for food.

07:03.978 --> 07:05.251
Been like family ever since.

07:05.792 --> 07:07.382
Did he have any enemies
that you know of?

07:07.967 --> 07:09.390
He had a bad-boy
image from the show,

07:09.510 --> 07:10.868
but he was actually sweet.

07:11.291 --> 07:13.886
Winning "Kitchen Wars" must
have been huge for him.

07:14.006 --> 07:14.902
How was he handling it?

07:15.200 --> 07:17.357
He loved it-- the fame,
the fortune.

07:17.477 --> 07:20.132
It was everything he ever
dreamed of, e-except...

07:20.407 --> 07:21.411
Except what?

07:21.531 --> 07:23.897
I-I think he might have had
some financial troubles.

07:24.241 --> 07:25.078
What do you mean?

07:25.395 --> 07:27.590
When my dad passed
away a few months back,

07:27.710 --> 07:29.558
he left his restaurant
to Wolf and me.

07:29.678 --> 07:31.309
It was nothing fancy like Q3.

07:31.612 --> 07:33.030
It was just a little
diner in Queens.

07:34.129 --> 07:35.436
But about two weeks ago,

07:35.556 --> 07:37.167
he came to me asking
if I would buy him out.

07:37.609 --> 07:39.769
I tried to talk him out of it.

07:39.889 --> 07:41.337
I even told him that I
would loan him the money,

07:41.457 --> 07:42.612
but he refused.

07:43.190 --> 07:46.841
And in the end, I gave in
and I bought out his share.

07:47.202 --> 07:49.627
For how much? $40,000.

07:49.987 --> 07:51.857
Didn't he just win a lot
of money on "Kitchen Wars"?

07:51.977 --> 07:53.879
Well, he put it all
into the new restaurant.

07:53.999 --> 07:55.955
I tried to tell him to
hold some of it back,

07:56.075 --> 07:58.720
but he was an
all-or-nothing kind of guy.

08:01.933 --> 08:03.316
<i>Jennifer, Wolf,</i>

08:03.436 --> 08:06.629
<i>we've scored your dishes,
and although it was very close,</i>

08:07.265 --> 08:08.339
<i>Balthazar Wolf,</i>

08:08.459 --> 08:10.386
<i>you're the winner of "Kitchen Wars,
New York!"</i>

08:11.013 --> 08:12.446
<i>Yeah!</i>

08:13.328 --> 08:14.632
Look at his face.

08:15.514 --> 08:17.220
See how happy he is? Hmm.

08:17.340 --> 08:19.967
He had no idea in eight months,
he'd be dead.

08:20.989 --> 08:22.323
Well, the bank has the warrant,

08:22.324 --> 08:24.126
so we should have his
financials in a couple of hours.

08:24.694 --> 08:26.183
If he was having money troubles,
we'll find out.

08:26.303 --> 08:27.234
Beckett.

08:27.354 --> 08:30.073
Hey, how'd it go with the
late-night soup maker?

08:30.193 --> 08:31.985
You guys find him? Oh,
we found him all right.

08:32.506 --> 08:35.279
In line at the airport with $5,
000 cash in his suitcase

08:35.280 --> 08:36.727
and a one-way ticket to Ecuador.

08:37.049 --> 08:39.049
Mm. Nothing says "I'm guilty"

08:39.051 --> 08:40.770
like an attempt to
flee the country.

